id: pm-rkie
title: "Core read/validate integrity: exact-ID search rank guarantee across modes + parent-hierarchy cycle detection"
description: "Two agent-trust correctness bugs surfaced from dogfooding the large (1463-item) 2d-bots tracker: (GH-281) pm search <exact-id> returns the item but in HYBRID/SEMANTIC mode the exact-ID keyword boost (score 1000) is normalized to [0,1] and blended under hybrid_semantic_weight, so a high-semantic body-mention item can out-rank the exact target (keyword-only mode already fixed by #268/d31780c1 + covered by search-command.spec exact-id test); (GH-280) pm validate detects blocked_by/definition_of_ready dependency cycles (Tarjan SCC, #271) but NOT cycles in the parent (composition) graph, so A->parent->B->parent->A silently corrupts hierarchy rendering/orphan analysis/rollups. Bundled because both are core read+validate integrity fixes that determine whether agents can trust pm's primitives. Reuses existing primitives: combineHybridHits/scoreDocument for search, findLifecycleDependencyCycleComponents (generic Tarjan) for the parent graph."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 1
tags: []
